HEADWORD: Maraschino
<hw>Ma`ra*schi"no</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[It., fr.
<ets>marasca</ets>, <ets>amarasca</ets>, a sour cherry, L.
<ets>amarus</ets> bitter.]</ety> <def>A liqueur distilled from fermented
cherry juice, and flavored with the pit of a variety of cherry which
grows in Dalmatia.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

